# Environment Variables Reference

Copy this to your `.env` file for local development and deployment.

```bash
# ============================================================================
# REDDIT API CREDENTIALS
# ============================================================================
# Get from https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=your_reddit_client_id_here
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=your_reddit_client_secret_here


# ============================================================================
# MODEL CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
BERT_MODEL_DIR=./output/binary_model/final_model
CALIBRATION_ARTIFACT=./calibration_artifacts.json
GOVERNANCE_CONFIG=./governance_config.json
DRIFT_BASELINE=./drift_baseline.pkl


# ============================================================================
# DATA RETENTION & LOGGING
# ============================================================================
DATA_RETENTION_DAYS=30
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
```

## Notes

### Reddit Credentials
1. Go to https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
2. Scroll down - Click "Create another app"
3. Name: "AI4MH Crisis Monitor"
4. Choose "script"
5. Copy **Client ID** and **Client Secret**


### For Local Development
```bash
# Create .env in project root
cd Real-Time-Geospatial-Crisis-Monitor
touch .env
# Edit with your values
nano .env

# Python will load automatically via python-dotenv
```